  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Facilitating access to clean and safe drinking water to conflict-affected communities in Idleb &#x2013;2021-2022</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">GOAL proposes to provide lifesaving safe water to 108,104 vulnerable individuals in Idleb Governorate, North West Syria. This will be implemented via the provision of essential support to 9 Water Stations (WSs) and 3 Water Units (WUs). GOAL has extensive experience delivering water supply programming in Idleb since 2014. In 2020 GOAL provided clean safe water to the homes of over one million people in Idleb via 66 water stations and 4 water units. The proposed project builds upon the experience of having successfully delivered several similar projects with OCHA, FCDO, and BHA funding. 
The aim of the action is to ensure access to reliable, safe, and clean drinking water to vulnerable conflict-affected communities including host and displaced populations in three high priority northern sub-districts of Idleb Governorate (Qourqeena, Darkosh and Armanaz). Core activities will include procurement of fuel, minor infrastructure rehabilitation, training to water station operators, coaching to WUs, water quality monitoring and hygiene promotion. 
The proposed action will enable approximately 108,104 people living in the targeted areas to access a sufficient quantity of clean and safe drinking water. Following WASH cluster standards, 35 litres/person/day (LPD) will be piped directly to households (HH) to ensure equitable access for all community members. 
In target areas, to complement the water supply activities, 5,000 people&#x2014;including school children, WU staff and individuals benefiting from GOAL food or cash distributions under other grants will be reached with essential hygiene promotion sessions adapted to COVID-19 best working practices as outlined by the WASH cluster. Themes covered will include water safety, conservation, and safe hygiene.</narrative>
  </description>
